content: Wonderful game!! Interesting and makes you think. Nothing else it that I have found!

content: This game is an art piece that's good at creating a mood. The puzzles are not as challenging as some other games, and its production values are sometimes uneven, but that is okay! Excellent game, the only mobile game for which I've actually sat through the credits. Puzzles aren't overly confusing, the difficulty doesn't scale horribly as you continue but remains a challenge throughput. The story is intriguing and draws you through the puzzle to keep playing.

I'm sorry, I know you're a small team and I usually support the good devs because the store needs them, you guys made a great game but the puzzles or mini-games, whatever you want to call them were just annoying. Each time I completed a few I hoped it was the last but they would go on and on. The satellite one almost did me in but then the aliens did it, they were not fun to solve, it was aggravating. It was always pot-shots hoping to get lucky and there were far too many in succession. Sorry.

Creative Short story, with original yet repetitive puzzles to the point of monotony. No hints available so u MUST solve the puzzles/patterns to advance. Almost tapped out and uninstalled a couple of times from boredom caused by restarting the same puzzle DOZENS OF TIMES. Only from brute stubborness and expectation of sharing my opinion in a review, was i able to force myself to open the game a few times a week to progress. Not how games are supposed to feel...
replyContent:
Hello Christine,

We're sorry you found the puzzles repetitive.

The game has hints, you can enable them the first time you start the game or at any time in the options menu.

Thank you for playing!

You can tell a lot of love went into making this game, I played all the way through. I wish the plot and lore of the world were more developed, and the puzzles were a means to story exploration rather than the primary game. Then I could see it having a lot more replayability. I can tell there's a lot of fun easter eggs, but I don't feel like going through all of the puzzles to find them. A saved game function would be a great ad in.

Very cool, very different, very avante garde, very aural. Surreal landscapes lightly seasoned with an alien breed of enigmal exercises to remind me I'm a part of this story, my presence alien in itself and lightly disconnected, like reading in a dream - are those even words? And if not why do I understand them? Or do I? Do I understand anything? Has anybody seen my robot? We sat down by a repair terminal to get some rest for a bit. Why was I so tired? And then there was this game, I think...
replyContent: Thank you, you made our day!

content: I got this through Play Pass, so I only kind of paid for it. It is a great game, though fairly short. Maybe 2-3hours of game play. Nice story and interesting puzzles. It isn't super difficult for puzzle game enthusiasts.

I'm not the brightest bulb, though, so my need to consult a walk-through 4-5 times could be up to user error, I won't dock it for my own inabilities as opposed to it being a downfall. Overall, if I could give it a 4.5, I would. Interesting and engaging, however sometimes monotonous. I would recommend!
